sql:
SELECT company_size, AVG(salary_in_usd) AS avg_salary_in_usd
FROM job_market_data
GROUP BY company_size;

SELECT AVG(salary_in_usd) AS average_salary_in_usd
FROM job_market_data
WHERE remote_ratio = 50;

SELECT AVG(salary_in_usd) AS average_salary_in_usd
FROM job_market_data
WHERE employment_type = 'FT' AND industry = 'Technology';

external_knowledge:
- Total compensation is the sum of salary, bonus, and benefits value, converted to USD using the exchange rate; 
- Remote work ratio refers to the percentage of work allowed to be done remotely; 
- Company size categories are defined by the number of employees (e.g., small, medium, large).

sql:
SELECT job_title
FROM job_market_data
WHERE employment_type = 'PT';

external_knowledge:
- Experienced levels refer to employees with experience level 'EX' (Executive) or 'SE' (Senior Executive); 
- Large companies are those with company_size 'L'; 
- Employment types include 'FT' (Full-time) and 'PT' (Part-time).
